column5: Ahhhh quit your whining and get to work. At least you got to have a week at Lacair.  Sounds like a wonderful time was had by all, wish I could have been part of it but a man with a sharp knife had other plans for me. I will be there next year no matter what!

As you can see the quote above is he wants to see....... not that it happened. However if it would raise enough money for the walleye fund next year I might consider doing it.  Thanks for a great time at LA dawg I am sure you will get back into the work swing again.   Art
Get back to work Dawg!  I don't feel a bit sorry for ya.  Art at least the man has vision   albeit a weird one!    Whopper

Glen...it was a true pleasure meeting you at Lakair this year!  I now understand why you'd drive all that way to fish as well.  Glad to see you made it home safely...and as far as work is concerned...you think you have it bad?  It's going to be just as hot here as it is there today, and the air conditioning in the office was turned lower to conserve energy!! Can you believe that!!!! LOL
Glen,glad you made it home alright,was good to see you again,till next year.Thanks again Bubba.  Art,don,t even think about doing that,that would be something scary to see  Steve
roasting in 93* heat in a 40' deep excavation wearing a hard hat, steel toed boots, ear plugs, safety glasses, and gloves sounds a little better than   Great to see you Greencoach, till next year..
I feel your pain Glen.........Somehow, thinkin' about one of those Virginia boys in their shorts is a little too much to bare.......'scuse the pun!
Hmm... what I don't understand is that ..  why the pickeral in the morning turns to walleye in the evening...  I have to try this Lakair thing one day...
AAWWwwww Poor Dawg...  If he doesn't cheer up soon...should we have him put down ???

AW W W W what a shame!! 40' hole? is that for the new Outhouse We got a Humidex of about 104degs, so I'm inside, suffering for you Guy's and think of the days I had to do it. NO FUN!  So glad I got to meet you Glen, after all the chats we had online.Even tho' I had trouble with that Southern drawl   Hope to get to see ya next year!!!
Glen, did they really let you go north from the deep south to party with them damn yankees
Young man I was once in your shoes!

Ha, here I am crawling out of bed at 2:00am to start my miserable day back in the big smoke...at 7:00 am I was stuck in traffic on the 401 an hour and a half into my shift, with my shirt already wet from the perspiration, thinking I should be sitting down to breakfast making my plans as to where I was going to go Pike hunting...go ahead Dawg, sing me the blues why don't ya???  Maureen

Hahahah Dawg.... I think alot of feel your pain... It was damned HOT in those big rigs today too and I kept thinking the same.... LAKAIR PLEASE... lol  Glad to see you made it home... Thanks again for the fish...  Hugz  Shelley
Relax Dawg...this needle is for pricking my finger to get a blood glucose reading on my monitor...  Sympathy is right between sh** and syphillis in the dictionary so you don't need none of those...
Can't do it Dawg, don't think the bosses would be impressed, and I wouldn't want to scare the customers...  Maureen
All I can say is .Dawg..suck it up and do your job!Any more whinin and I'm gonna send you down the road totin yer lunch bucket! Joe
LOL Glen, but I kissed them and made them feel better!
